      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but you keep saying \"the priority must be fiscal discipline\" like it's an objective fact. some economists argue that debt is actually manageable if the growth rate stays higher than the interest rate, and that cutting spending during a crisis actually makes things worse by killing demand. why does your analysis make debt reduction seem like a prerequisite rather than just one of several competing economic theories?",
